<chapter><title>RexxGTK Function Reference</title>
<indexterm><primary>Functions</primary></indexterm>

<para>There are a small number of routines available in the RexxGTK package.
These routines are divided into two groups. The first group is used to control the
GTK+ system message looping mechanism and provide GTK+ initialization. The second group
of routines are general and provide useful information or access to operating system
functions.</para>

